articles.author: Pesha Magid, Samia Nakhoul, Suleiman Al-Khalidi, Nafisa Eltahir
articles.description: Saudi Arabia is spearheading urgent Arab efforts to develop a plan for Gaza's future as a counter to U.S. President Donald Trump's ambition for a Middle East Riviera cleared of its Palestinian inhabitants, 10 sources said.
articles.title: Insight: Saudi Arabia spearheads Arab scramble for alternative to Trump's Gaza plan

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt, David Brunnstrom, Nandita Bose
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump said on Thursday that Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi had offered to talk about easingtariffs, buying more U.S. oil, gas and combat aircraft, concessions that may deter a trade war.
articles.title: India's Modi and Trump agree to trade talks to lower tensions

articles.author: Andrea Shalal, David Lawder, Susan Heavey
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump said he plans to unveil reciprocal tariffs on Thursday afternoon but gave no details about his latest tariff plan, which could take aim at every country that charges duties on U.S. imports.
articles.title: Trump says reciprocal tariffs coming on Thursday

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Pope Francis was taken to hospital on Friday morning for tests and to continue treatment of his ongoing bronchitis, the Vatican said.
articles.title: Pope Francis taken to hospital for bronchitis treatment

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Four people died in a fire in a resort construction site in South Korea's port city of Busan, the News1 news agency reported on Friday.
articles.title: Four dead at resort construction site fire in Busan, South Korea, media says

articles.author: Sabine Siebold, Andrew Gray
articles.description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy is expected to meet U.S. Vice President JD Vance in Munich on Friday after Donald Trump startled U.S. allies by calling Vladimir Putin and announcing the start of talks to end the war in Ukraine.
articles.title: Zelenskiy expected to meet Vance in Munich as security conference begins

articles.author: Lucy Papachristou
articles.description: Last August, a middle-aged Russian woman with her face covered walked onto Red Square in Moscow and, in the shadow of the Kremlin, scattered handfuls of coloured rubber balls on the cobblestones below.
articles.title: Russia pursues Navalny supporters, one year after opposition leader's death

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Kremlin on Friday dismissed as a "provocation" accusations by Ukraine that a Russian drone had damaged the containment shelter at the Chornobyl nuclear power plant overnight.
articles.title: Kremlin dismisses Ukraine's accusation that Russia attacked Chornobyl nuclear plant

articles.author: Daniel Trotta
articles.description: President Donald Trump's transgender policy began with a Day One executive order delegitimizing gender identity. Now it has encroached on a conspicuous place, removing the word "transgender" from the U.S. National Park Service website for the Stonewall National Monument.
articles.title: Trump erasure of transgender references extends to Stonewall monument website

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: German prosecutors are treating the case of a man who drove a car into a crowd in Munich on Thursday as a murder attempt, the prosecutor's office and the police said in a joint statement on Friday.
articles.title: Munich car ramming treated as murder attempt, prosecutors say
